text: Garfield County is a county in Washington in the United States. The county seat is Pomeroy. At the 2020 census, 2,286 people lived there, which makes it the least populous county in Washington; with about , it is also the least densely populated county in Washington. ==References== Category:1881 establishments in the United States Category:1880s establishments in Washington (state) Category:Washington (state) counties
title: Garfield County, Washington
